390
00:41:25,216 --> 00:41:27,514
He has bought the Vettayapuram palace

391
00:41:28,385 --> 00:41:32,287
Everyone is scared when a mention
is made about the palace

392
00:41:32,556 --> 00:41:35,525
What is there? What happened?

393
00:41:35,726 --> 00:41:39,423
About 100 to 150 years ago...

394
00:41:40,064 --> 00:41:43,363
<i>King Vettayan lived in that palace</i>

395
00:41:43,567 --> 00:41:48,095
<i>He used to make a peculiar noise
when he arrives</i>

396
00:41:48,572 --> 00:41:53,703
<i>He would do anything to attain his goal.
He was such a brutal man</i>

397
00:41:54,245 --> 00:41:59,706
<i>Once when he had gone to
Vijayanagaram in Andhra...</i>

398
00:42:00,084 --> 00:42:04,384
<i>he met a dancer called Chandramukhi</i>

399
00:42:04,588 --> 00:42:10,049
<i>He was lured by her beauty and
wanted to make her his mistress</i>

400
00:42:10,928 --> 00:42:13,556
<i>But Chandramukhi did not agree</i>

401
00:42:13,764 --> 00:42:19,066
Because she already loved
a dancer called Gunasekaran

402
00:42:19,270 --> 00:42:25,402
Even after knowing that, the king
abducted her against her wishes

403
00:42:25,609 --> 00:42:28,737
Chandramukhi without the knowledge
of the king...

404
00:42:28,946 --> 00:42:36,250
made Gunasekaran stay in
a nearby house and met him stealthily

405
00:42:36,453 --> 00:42:40,583
The King came to know about this.
On a Durgastami day...

406
00:42:40,958 --> 00:42:47,921
the king killed Gunasekaran
right in front of her...

407
00:42:48,132 --> 00:42:51,101
in the banquet hall of the palace,
and he burnt her alive

408
00:42:51,302 --> 00:42:54,760
Chandramukhi had an untimely death
not doing anything wrong

409
00:42:54,972 --> 00:42:57,600
Her soul wanted to avenge the king

410
00:42:57,808 --> 00:43:02,268
The king knew about this and brought
all sorcerors from all over the country...

411
00:43:02,479 --> 00:43:08,111
and conducted prayers and sealed
Chandramukhi's ashes in a pot

412
00:43:08,319 --> 00:43:12,119
He kept the pot in a room at the southern
corner of the palace and locked it

413
00:43:12,323 --> 00:43:17,784
After some years the king also died.
But Chandramukhi's soul...

414
00:43:17,995 --> 00:43:22,125
is still waiting in that room
to avenge the king

415
00:43:22,333 --> 00:43:28,966
It is said that there is a
king cobra there too

416
00:43:29,340 --> 00:43:34,300
<i>Nobody knows how much of this
is true and how much is not</i>

417
00:44:12,883 --> 00:44:16,250
12 o'clock? This is the time
at which the ghosts come out

418
00:44:17,721 --> 00:44:20,189
They have all left me alone.
Is it a bedroom?

419
00:44:20,391 --> 00:44:23,360
It looks like a big ground.
I accepted not knowing this

420
00:44:24,228 --> 00:44:27,026
Now my heart throbs while I sleep here

421
00:44:29,733 --> 00:44:30,529
Who is that?

422
00:44:31,235 --> 00:44:32,031
Oh God

423
00:44:33,737 --> 00:44:35,864
I didn't do it, I didn't do it

424
00:44:36,073 --> 00:44:39,702
It is me, Murugesan

425
00:44:39,910 --> 00:44:44,870
Why did you come at this time?
- Could not bear my wife's snores

426
00:44:45,082 --> 00:44:48,051
At nights she walks like a devil,
she lies down like a ghost

427
00:44:48,252 --> 00:44:50,379
From the day I heard the
priest's story I have lost my sleep

428
00:44:50,587 --> 00:44:52,612
Let us hug together and sleep here

429
00:44:55,092 --> 00:44:58,960
No.
- Expected. Are you not a doctor?

430
00:44:59,763 --> 00:45:01,890
Please clarify my doubts.
- What Murughesan?

431
00:45:02,099 --> 00:45:04,727
Do ghosts exist?

432
00:45:06,437 --> 00:45:08,234
Have they ever seen one?

433
00:45:08,939 --> 00:45:11,407
Should I believe it or not?
I want to know this

434
00:45:15,279 --> 00:45:18,908
Why do you turn so often?
It seems the priest is better than you

435
00:45:19,116 --> 00:45:23,177
Do ghosts exist? Is there any
indication of a ghost coming?

436
00:45:23,454 --> 00:45:28,084
There are typical indications.
- Like?

437
00:45:28,292 --> 00:45:30,760
A dog howls at a distance

438
00:45:37,134 --> 00:45:40,262
Really, I can hear the sound there

439
00:45:40,471 --> 00:45:42,439
Did I ask?
- No

440
00:45:43,640 --> 00:45:48,600
The breeze blows wild,
the trees sway...

441
00:45:48,979 --> 00:45:50,446
the windows rattle...

442
00:45:54,485 --> 00:45:57,113
I can hear this sound there

443
00:45:57,488 --> 00:45:58,955
Did I ask?
- No

444
00:45:59,156 --> 00:46:02,956
A faint smell of jasmine...

445
00:46:03,160 --> 00:46:04,787
Jasmine!
- Why are you shouting?

446
00:46:04,995 --> 00:46:08,453
Ok, the wind will carry jasmine smell

447
00:46:09,500 --> 00:46:13,800
Yes I can smell the jamine fragrance

448
00:46:14,004 --> 00:46:15,130
Did I ask?
- No

449
00:46:15,339 --> 00:46:18,638
Just hear the story, no cross questions

450
00:46:19,009 --> 00:46:22,638
If you do... what is this?
- Adam's apple

451
00:46:22,846 --> 00:46:24,245
I will pluck it out

452
00:46:25,682 --> 00:46:26,580
Then...

453
00:46:27,851 --> 00:46:28,977
What?

454
00:46:29,853 --> 00:46:32,151
What?
- Anklet

455
00:46:35,526 --> 00:46:38,495
Oh God I hear the anklet sound also

456
00:46:38,695 --> 00:46:40,822
Did I ask?
- No

457
00:46:41,198 --> 00:46:47,262
Then a smoke like image in
white attire comes up

458
00:46:49,373 --> 00:46:54,333
It's showing up!

459
00:46:54,545 --> 00:46:56,740
Where?
- There

460
00:46:58,215 --> 00:47:06,020
Why do you laugh like a woman?
- Not I. The ghost is laughing

461
00:47:06,223 --> 00:47:08,350
Where?
- There

462
00:47:17,234 --> 00:47:19,293
It's gone

463
00:47:20,571 --> 00:47:24,029
You have mistaken my grandpa's dhoti
swinging in the wind for a ghost

464
00:47:24,241 --> 00:47:26,766
Have you not learnt anything?
- Me scared?

465
00:47:27,578 --> 00:47:28,875
Me?
- Yes

466
00:47:30,247 --> 00:47:33,876
Murugesan and I were rehearsing
for a drama. What is you name?

467
00:47:34,084 --> 00:47:35,711
Why?
